title: 2020 United States presidential election in Oklahoma
added: [[Donald Trump]]'s win in the [[Oklahoma's 2nd congressional district|2nd congressional district]], by a margin of 54%, was his biggest victory in the [[Oklahoma's congressional districts|state's five congressional districts]]. The 2nd district has the highest proportion of Native Americans in the state.  While [[Joe Biden]] fared better with Native American voters in several other Western states, such as [[Nevada]], [[Arizona]], [[New Mexico]], and [[Montana]], Donald Trump carried the Native vote in Oklahoma decisively.{{Citation needed|date=January 2021}}
